@startuml sequence-login
title Séquence — Login + rotation refresh token

actor User
participant "LoginPage" as UI
participant "AuthContext" as Ctx
participant "ApiClient" as Api
participant "auth.controller" as Ctrl
participant "auth.service" as Svc
database "Prisma / Neon" as DB

User -> UI : saisit email + mdp
UI -> Ctx : login(email, password)
Ctx -> Api : POST /auth/login
Api -> Ctrl : body { email, password }
Ctrl -> Svc : login(email, password)
Svc -> DB : findUser(email)
DB --> Svc : User { passwordHash }
Svc -> Svc : bcrypt.compare()
Svc -> Svc : signJWT(15min)\nsignRefreshToken(30j)
Svc -> DB : insert RefreshToken
DB --> Svc : ok
Svc --> Ctrl : { accessToken, refreshToken, user }
Ctrl --> Api : 200 OK
Api --> Ctx : tokens
Ctx -> Ctx : localStorage.set(access, refresh)
Ctx --> UI : success → navigate(/dashboard)

== Plus tard : access token expiré ==

UI -> Api : GET /vehicles (Bearer expiré)
Api -> Ctrl : request
Ctrl --> Api : 401 Unauthorized

note over Api : _refreshPromise évite\nles refresh parallèles
Api -> Ctrl : POST /auth/refresh\n{ refreshToken }
Ctrl -> Svc : refresh(token)
Svc -> DB : find RefreshToken (valid, !expired)
DB --> Svc : ok
Svc -> DB : delete old refreshToken
Svc -> Svc : sign new pair
Svc -> DB : insert new RefreshToken
Svc --> Ctrl : { accessToken, refreshToken }
Ctrl --> Api : 200
Api -> Api : localStorage.update()
Api -> Ctrl : retry GET /vehicles (Bearer neuf)
Ctrl --> Api : 200 [vehicles]
Api --> UI : data

== Logout ==

UI -> Api : POST /auth/logout
Api -> Ctrl : { refreshToken }
Ctrl -> Svc : logout(token)
Svc -> DB : delete RefreshToken
Svc --> Ctrl : ok
Ctrl --> Api : 204
Api -> Api : localStorage.clear()

@enduml
